verses.text_plain: Woe to thee that spoilest, and thou wast not spoiled; and dealest treacherously, and they dealt not treacherously with thee! when thou shalt cease to spoil, thou shalt be spoiled; and when thou shalt make an end to deal treacherously, they shall deal treacherously with thee.
verses.verse_html: 1Woe to thee that spoilest, and thou wast not spoiled; and dealest treacherously, and they dealt not treacherously with thee! when thou shalt cease to spoil, thou shalt be spoiled; and when thou shalt make an end to deal treacherously, they shall deal treacherously with thee.

tokens.text: with thee! when thou shalt cease
when thou shalt make an end

verses.text_plain: O Lord, be gracious unto us; we have waited for thee: be thou their arm every morning, our salvation also in the time of trouble.
verses.verse_html: 2O Lord, be gracious unto us; we have waited for thee: be thou their arm every morning, our salvation also in the time of trouble.

tokens.text: for thee: be thou their arm

verses.text_plain: At the noise of the tumult the people fled; at the lifting up of thyself the nations were scattered.
verses.verse_html: 3At the noise of the tumult the people fled; at the lifting up of thyself the nations were scattered.

verses.text_plain: And your spoil shall be gathered like the gathering of the caterpiller: as the running to and fro of locusts shall he run upon them.
verses.verse_html: 4And your spoil shall be gathered like the gathering of the caterpiller: as the running to and fro of locusts shall he run upon them.

tokens.text: as the running to and fro

verses.text_plain: The Lord is exalted; for he dwelleth on high: he hath filled Zion with judgment and righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 5The Lord is exalted; for he dwelleth on high: he hath filled Zion with judgment and righteousness.

verses.text_plain: And wisdom and knowledge shall be the stability of thy times, and strength of salvation: the fear of the Lord is his treasure.
verses.verse_html:
6And wisdom and knowledge shall be the stability of thy times, and strength of salvation: the fear of the Lord is his treasure. ▼
▼ salvation: Heb. salvations

verses.text_plain: Behold, their valiant ones shall cry without: the ambassadors of peace shall weep bitterly.
verses.verse_html:
7Behold, their valiant ones shall cry without: the ambassadors of peace shall weep bitterly. ▼
▼ valiant…: or, messengers

verses.text_plain: The highways lie waste, the wayfaring man ceaseth: he hath broken the covenant, he hath despised the cities, he regardeth no man.
verses.verse_html: 8The highways lie waste, the wayfaring man ceaseth: he hath broken the covenant, he hath despised the cities, he regardeth no man.

verses.text_plain: The earth mourneth and languisheth: Lebanon is ashamed and hewn down: Sharon is like a wilderness; and Bashan and Carmel shake off their fruits.
verses.verse_html:
9The earth mourneth and languisheth: Lebanon is ashamed and hewn down: Sharon is like a wilderness; and Bashan and Carmel shake off their fruits. ▼
▼ hewn…: or, withered away

footnotes.body_html: ▼ hewn…: or, withered away

verses.text_plain: Now will I rise, saith the Lord; now will I be exalted; now will I lift up myself.
verses.verse_html: 10Now will I rise, saith the Lord; now will I be exalted; now will I lift up myself.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall conceive chaff, ye shall bring forth stubble: your breath, as fire, shall devour you.
verses.verse_html: 11Ye shall conceive chaff, ye shall bring forth stubble: your breath, as fire, shall devour you.

verses.text_plain: And the people shall be as the burnings of lime: as thorns cut up shall they be burned in the fire.
verses.verse_html: 12And the people shall be as the burnings of lime: as thorns cut up shall they be burned in the fire.

verses.text_plain: Hear, ye that are far off, what I have done; and, ye that are near, acknowledge my might.
verses.verse_html: 13Hear, ye that are far off, what I have done; and, ye that are near, acknowledge my might.

verses.text_plain: The sinners in Zion are afraid; fearfulness hath surprised the hypocrites. Who among us shall dwell with the devouring fire? who among us shall dwell with everlasting burnings?
verses.verse_html: 14The sinners in Zion are afraid; fearfulness hath surprised the hypocrites. Who among us shall dwell with the devouring fire? who among us shall dwell with everlasting burnings?

verses.text_plain: He that walketh righteously, and speaketh uprightly; he that despiseth the gain of oppressions, that shaketh his hands from holding of bribes, that stoppeth his ears from hearing of blood, and shutteth his eyes from seeing evil;
verses.verse_html:
15He that walketh righteously, and speaketh uprightly; he that despiseth the gain of oppressions, that shaketh his hands from holding of bribes, that stoppeth his ears from hearing of blood, and shutteth his eyes from seeing evil; ▼
▼ righteously: Heb. in righteousnesses
 , ▼
▼ uprightly: Heb. uprightnesses
 , ▼
▼ oppressions: or, deceits
 , ▼
▼ blood: Heb. bloods

footnotes.body_html: ▼ righteously: Heb. in righteousnesses

verses.text_plain: He shall dwell on high: his place of defence shall be the munitions of rocks: bread shall be given him; his waters shall be sure.
verses.verse_html:
16He shall dwell on high: his place of defence shall be the munitions of rocks: bread shall be given him; his waters shall be sure. ▼
▼ high: Heb. heights, or, high places

footnotes.body_text: ▼ high: Heb. heights, or, high places
footnotes.body_html: ▼ high: Heb. heights, or, high places

verses.text_plain: Thine eyes shall see the king in his beauty: they shall behold the land that is very far off.
verses.verse_html:
17Thine eyes shall see the king in his beauty: they shall behold the land that is very far off. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. of far distances

footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. of far distances

verses.text_plain: Thine heart shall meditate terror. Where is the scribe? where is the receiver? where is he that counted the towers?
verses.verse_html:
18Thine heart shall meditate terror. Where is the scribe? where is the receiver? where is he that counted the towers? ▼
▼ receiver: Heb. weigher?

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not see a fierce people, a people of a deeper speech than thou canst perceive; of a stammering tongue, that thou canst not understand.
verses.verse_html:
19Thou shalt not see a fierce people, a people of a deeper speech than thou canst perceive; of a stammering tongue, that thou canst not understand. ▼
▼ stammering: or, ridiculous

verses.text_plain: Look upon Zion, the city of our solemnities: thine eyes shall see Jerusalem a quiet habitation, a tabernacle that shall not be taken down; not one of the stakes thereof shall ever be removed, neither shall any of the cords thereof be broken.
verses.verse_html: 20Look upon Zion, the city of our solemnities: thine eyes shall see Jerusalem a quiet habitation, a tabernacle that shall not be taken down; not one of the stakes thereof shall ever be removed, neither shall any of the cords thereof be broken.

tokens.text: neither shall any of the cords

verses.text_plain: But there the glorious Lord will be unto us a place of broad rivers and streams; wherein shall go no galley with oars, neither shall gallant ship pass thereby.
verses.verse_html:
21But there the glorious Lord will be unto us a place of broad rivers and streams; wherein shall go no galley with oars, neither shall gallant ship pass thereby. ▼
▼ of…: Heb. broad of spaces, or, hands

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of…: Heb. broad of spaces, or, hands
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: Heb. broad of spaces, or, hands

verses.text_plain: For the Lord is our judge, the Lord is our lawgiver, the Lord is our king; he will save us.
verses.verse_html:
22For the Lord is our judge, the Lord is our lawgiver, the Lord is our king; he will save us. ▼
▼ lawgiver: Heb. statutemaker

verses.text_plain: Thy tacklings are loosed; they could not well strengthen their mast, they could not spread the sail: then is the prey of a great spoil divided; the lame take the prey.
verses.verse_html:
23Thy tacklings are loosed; they could not well strengthen their mast, they could not spread the sail: then is the prey of a great spoil divided; the lame take the prey. ▼
▼ Thy…: or, They have forsaken thy tacklings

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Thy…: or, They have forsaken thy tacklings
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Thy…: or, They have forsaken thy tacklings

verses.text_plain: And the inhabitant shall not say, I am sick: the people that dwell therein shall be forgiven their iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 24And the inhabitant shall not say, I am sick: the people that dwell therein shall be forgiven their iniquity.
